title: Alpha-Mannosidosis: Prevalence and Demographics
short_description: Clinical document detailing the prevalence rate and demographic distribution of alpha-mannosidosis in the general population.
long_description: This clinical research document provides epidemiological data on alpha-mannosidosis, a rare genetic disorder. The document establishes the prevalence rate at 1 in 500,000 individuals in the general population and describes the demographic characteristics of affected individuals. It notes that the condition affects males and females equally and has the potential to impact individuals across all ethnic groups globally, indicating no gender or ethnic predisposition for this rare lysosomal storage disorder.
